1
00:00:29,710 --> 00:00:33,850
I go to meet her every night in my dreams.

2
00:00:37,250 --> 00:00:40,150
Bok Sil, I'm sleepy.

3
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:42,220
You can't, you can't, you can't!

4
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:49,180
When my memory comes back, I'll find your little brother for you.

5
00:00:49,180 --> 00:00:51,320
Just trust me.

6
00:00:53,430 --> 00:00:56,810
Sleep well, Louis.

7
00:00:56,810 --> 00:01:00,430
I'll definitely find Bok Nam for you. Just trust me.

8
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:09,290
But it's okay because we're together. I'll protect you.

9
00:01:09,290 --> 00:01:11,120
So just trust me.

10
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:21,450
I cry every night, because I miss the woman I see in my dreams,

11
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:27,070
but I can't go to her anymore.

12
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:30,850
My time has stopped,

13
00:01:31,850 --> 00:01:36,240
and I can't ever keep the promise that I made with her

14
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:39,460
to find her little brother.

15
00:01:40,260 --> 00:01:45,460
So I... can't go to her anymore.

16
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:49,620
Episode 11: The Dream Lover: - You In My Dream

17
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:57,400
One month later ...

18
00:02:02,770 --> 00:02:04,960
It's Maxim Gold.

19
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:14,920
Come eat.

20
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,340
Okay.

21
00:02:21,460 --> 00:02:24,520
Let's be strong today too, Bok Sil!

22
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:36,790
My Precious!

23
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:40,780
Tell me if there's anything that you want to eat.

24
00:02:40,780 --> 00:02:43,450
Your grandma will find it whatever it is and make it for you.

25
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,580
It's okay, Grandmother.

26
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:53,470
Louis, shouldn't you start going to the company now?

27
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:57,330
Yes ma'am, I understand.

28
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:04,000
But why did the headquarters director suddenly quit the company?

29
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,490
Did he get scouted by somewhere?

30
00:03:05,490 --> 00:03:07,850
He was my role model.

31
00:03:07,850 --> 00:03:10,110
I mean, how can he just quit and leave me here?

32
00:03:10,110 --> 00:03:12,920
Right? You should just quit now too.

33
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:18,200
- I mean, you already copy him from head to toe, so why can't you write your resignation letter like him too?
- That's right.

34
00:03:20,860 --> 00:03:26,650
Is it possible that the director resigned because Bok Sil quit?

35
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:34,870
Team Leader! Team Leader Baek!

36
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:38,990
Team Leader, it seems like you know something about it,

37
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:40,970
so please give us a tip.

38
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:44,820
I don't know why Headquarters Director Cha quit,

39
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:48,320
but another director will come here soon.

40
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,090
Who?

41
00:03:52,090 --> 00:03:55,350
- Shopping King Louis the 25th?
- What?!

42
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:04,540
That Chairwoman's grandson who came back from the dead?

43
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:07,080
Wa-Wang Louis?!

44
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:11,960
Yes! Yeah!

45
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,130
Wait, there are so many departments in the company. Why did he have to come here of all places?

46
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:18,400
- But I still got three stars at that time.
- I got two...

47
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:22,990
I got five stars! Five stars, five of them! Five stars!

48
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:28,400
Oh, I'm screwed.

49
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:36,570
- Hello.
- Oh my goodness...

50
00:04:36,570 --> 00:04:38,330
You're here?

51
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,460
- Welcome.
- Oh?!

52
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:43,800
It's Manager Lee Gyeong Gook.

53
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:49,910
- How did you know my name?
- I told you that I'd remember your name, Manager Lee Gyeong Gook.

54
00:04:49,910 --> 00:04:51,820
It's an honor.

55
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:56,550
Um... Your office is over there, Director. This way, please.

56
00:04:57,590 --> 00:04:59,120
No.

57
00:05:02,420 --> 00:05:04,660
I want to sit here.

58
00:05:46,570 --> 00:05:48,200
Please drink.

59
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,780
As expected, I don't have anyone, but you.

60
00:05:55,780 --> 00:05:57,530
You're the best!

61
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:09,450
Don't pay any attention to me and work comfortably.

62
00:06:09,450 --> 00:06:10,710
Yes, well...

63
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:13,420
Work comfortably, comfortably.

64
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:20,730
Yes.

65
00:06:21,810 --> 00:06:25,850
He definitely isn't normal.

66
00:06:25,850 --> 00:06:27,570
I'm going to go crazy, seriously!

67
00:06:27,570 --> 00:06:30,800
What the heck is he talking about, telling us not to worry about him, when he's sitting right next to us?

68
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,090
It's so burdensome.

69
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:35,150
Is he trying to keep an eye on us and see whether we're working or not?

70
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:37,100
Isn't he unexpectedly strict?

71
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:40,000
Bingo! I knew it from the moment he gave me one star.

72
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,020
He was kind of justified in doing so...

73
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:46,130
What is this, Darling? Are you taking Director Louie's side and dissing me?

74
00:06:46,130 --> 00:06:48,000
No.

75
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:52,380
If Bok Sil were here, I could at least have tried lobbying through her... Ah, I'm screwed, seriously.

76
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:55,610
Are Director Louis and Bok Sil broken up now?

77
00:06:55,610 --> 00:06:59,910
Probably. The gap between their social classes is way too big.

78
00:06:59,910 --> 00:07:04,110
But I wonder where Bok Sil is right now.

79
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:08,790
www.singsingline.com
Bean Basket Bean Sprouts

80
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:11,550
You've got a delivery!

81
00:07:22,420 --> 00:07:25,390
Did the director send it?

82
00:07:29,850 --> 00:07:31,750
So pretty!

83
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:47,630
It's pretty. Press on.

84
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:50,090
Thank you.

85
00:07:56,290 --> 00:07:58,690
When are you going to make my name plate?!

86
00:07:58,690 --> 00:08:00,790
Use this at least for now...

87
00:08:00,790 --> 00:08:02,930
Director & Investor Cha Joong Won

88
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:04,760
What is this?!

89
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:06,800
It's really lame, isn't it?

90
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,060
- Bring me the permanent marker.
- What?

91
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:10,900
Quickly!

92
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,980
Why are you laughing?

93
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:31,180
I mean... What kind of job title is Daddy Long Legs?

94
00:08:31,180 --> 00:08:33,680
It's better than Wild Ginseng Benefactor.

95
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:38,050
The office, the desk, and the computer all suck, and I get paid peanuts.

96
00:08:38,050 --> 00:08:40,750
I think I need a special job title to at least feel a little better.

97
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:46,560
When we make a lot of money and get a name plate later, make sure you put this on it, got it?

98
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,990
Yes!

99
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:51,240
What did you decide on for the site's opening item? Did you secure the producer?

100
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:55,140
Yes. I've decided on Goo Joon Pyo Cabbage which Mr. Goo Joon Pyo shed blood and sweat to grow. (Joke about the main character in Boys Over Flowers.)

101
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:59,380
We decided to make the quality top-notch since the product is named after the producer.

102
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:02,710
For now they have agreed to an exclusive distribution contract with our site.

103
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:06,060
The distribution industry has no choice but to resort to the direct sales method in the future.

104
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:08,900
From that perspective, singsingline.com (singsing means fresh in Korean),

105
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:11,620
which is an online produce direct sales site, has a great growth potential.

106
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:14,080
Do your best with your discerning eye to secure

107
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:17,490
high quality farm produce from reliable suppliers.

108
00:09:17,490 --> 00:09:18,800
- Yes, sir!
- Get to work!

109
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,370
Yes, sir.

110
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,600
You should eat lunch with Oppa In Seong.

111
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:42,710
What am I supposed to do when you come to my workplace and ask for food?

112
00:09:44,530 --> 00:09:47,480
Hyung In Seong left first because he was mad.

113
00:10:03,830 --> 00:10:06,130
Wow, this is delicious!

114
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:07,750
It's totally my style.

115
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,300
- You want to eat one more?
- Yeah!

116
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:18,560
That's right. Let's eat one more.

117
00:10:20,610 --> 00:10:22,270
Is this it?

118
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:26,870
Man, why did Joong Won leave a perfectly good company to go back and forth to this kind of place?

119
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:30,560
He must have a reason. Is Joong Won the type of guy to do something for no reason?

120
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:34,800
He kicked that pretty Team Leader Baek Ma Ri to the curb, then kicked his position as Goldline director to the curb!

121
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:37,080
He's kicking everything to the curb these days!

122
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:40,640
I seriously can't understand why a kid who never caused any trouble, even when he was a teenager, is doing this!

123
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:45,460
- He may be doing it now, because he didn't do it back then.
- What?!

124
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:48,870
Well, I'm just saying.

125
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,450
Excuse me.

126
00:10:57,450 --> 00:10:59,810
Oh, yes... Who are you?

127
00:10:59,810 --> 00:11:05,060
Um... Do you possibly know someone named Cha Joong Won?

128
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:07,480
Director, Investor Cha Joong Won

129
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:11,970
What is that?
[Daddy-Long-Legs]

130
00:11:11,970 --> 00:11:15,020
Isn't this kid seriously insane?!

131
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:27,630
So... You're saying that you're the president of singsingline.com?

132
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:29,640
And our Joong Won is the director?

133
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:32,020
Yes, that's right.

134
00:11:35,660 --> 00:11:41,160
It's weird, isn't it? I also don't understand why he's working at a place like this at all.

135
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:44,870
Young lady! I'll ask you directly.

136
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:48,500
What is your relationship with our Joong Won?

137
00:11:49,420 --> 00:11:52,380
You really look like a headquarters director wearing clothes like that.

138
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:54,410
I originally have a good sense of style.

139
00:11:54,410 --> 00:11:59,060
Ahjussi, I told you to look after Bok Sil well, but when did I tell you to quit the company?

140
00:11:59,060 --> 00:12:01,810
I'm asking why you're working at Bok Sil's company?

141
00:12:01,810 --> 00:12:03,630
It's my free will!

142
00:12:03,630 --> 00:12:08,610
I'm saying I'm going to live my life the way I want. What does it have to do with you?

143
00:12:08,610 --> 00:12:11,530
You should just look after Bok Sil well.

144
00:12:11,530 --> 00:12:15,470
You can't get any closer to her. Never. You understand, right?

145
00:12:15,470 --> 00:12:21,300
I don't want to. I'm going to stay stuck right to Bok Sil's side.

146
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:24,050
You just try it, seriously!

147
00:12:36,830 --> 00:12:38,690
Make sure you make it nice and strong.

148
00:12:38,690 --> 00:12:41,960
I got it, so stop nagging.

149
00:12:48,530 --> 00:12:53,080
But why are you putting three locks on a rooftop room?

150
00:12:53,730 --> 00:12:58,870
Jeez, what's it matter to you if I put three or four locks? It's my villa and my money.

151
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:04,540
In Seong's mom! What kind of money did you get that you bought this villa?

152
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:05,770
I won the lotto.

153
00:13:05,770 --> 00:13:10,360
Oh my word. What good deeds did you do in your previous life that you hit the jackpot?

154
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:12,950
Because I'm so introverted,

155
00:13:12,950 --> 00:13:14,760
I can't really tell people something they won't like.

156
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:18,210
My nickname was Sympathetic Lady Geum Ja when I was young.

157
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:23,560
My, my. You just do your job well.

158
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:34,510
- Please get in.
- Okay.

159
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:48,770
Where shall I take you?

160
00:13:48,770 --> 00:13:50,500
Let's go to the place we always go.

161
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:52,900
I understand. I will start the car.

162
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:57,280
Please mind your dignity, Director.

163
00:13:58,950 --> 00:14:00,800
So cringeworthy!

164
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:08,250
Mom, we're here!

165
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:15,720
Our Louis came? You look so cool!

166
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:21,250
Wait, Ms. Geum Ja. Aren't you fawning over Louis too much, when you pushed your own son aside?

167
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:23,330
Ahjumma, here.

168
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:25,130
Oh, what is it this time?

169
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:27,910
I bought yours, too, when I bought Bok Sil's.

170
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:32,270
Hyung In Seong told me not to buy yours. He said it would be a waste of money.

171
00:14:32,270 --> 00:14:35,690
Seriously, you're no help to my life at all.

172
00:14:35,690 --> 00:14:38,050
There's no way I can't adore you.

173
00:14:38,050 --> 00:14:41,220
You buy several of everything and share it with us.

174
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:44,870
He's the Shopping King, you know. He's generous.

175
00:14:44,870 --> 00:14:48,100
Did the locks get put on right? Bok Sil can't be in any danger.

176
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:52,490
Of course! I put three on there, since I thought you might worry.

177
00:14:53,210 --> 00:14:56,220
Make sure you check it. Mom's a good liar.

