179
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:26,290
♬ Far Away, I'm searching for myself again All Day ♬

180
00:15:26,290 --> 00:15:32,010
♬ All Day, In the smoky sunlight ♬

181
00:15:32,010 --> 00:15:37,080
♬ I ask again ♬

182
00:15:38,450 --> 00:15:44,050
♬ Which way should I go ♬

183
00:15:44,050 --> 00:15:48,960
♬ One exhausted step ♬

184
00:15:50,970 --> 00:15:53,780
♬ But I Can Fly  ♬

185
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:59,350
♬ Past countless stars Fly Away ♬

186
00:15:59,350 --> 00:16:01,410
♬ The space where memories fell asleep ♬

187
00:16:01,410 --> 00:16:05,540
Hey, go over there. When a man and a woman are different, why would you get so close to me?

188
00:16:05,540 --> 00:16:11,940
♬ Will I be able to wake up someday ♬

189
00:16:13,990 --> 00:16:17,060
♬ Lost The Way  ♬

190
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:20,080
I'm hungry. Give me some food.

191
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:23,160
♬ Oh Lost My Way  ♬

192
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:31,970
♬ Find The Way, I want to know. ♬

193
00:16:31,970 --> 00:16:34,190
♬ Let Me Know  ♬

194
00:16:34,190 --> 00:16:39,230
♬  These tears like paint spreading ♬

195
00:16:39,230 --> 00:16:41,130
Hey!

196
00:16:41,130 --> 00:16:45,880
♬ Is there an end, perhaps ♬

197
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:55,900
It's already time for Bok Sil to come home.

198
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:05,900
♬ When I opened my eyes again ♬

199
00:17:06,970 --> 00:17:14,040
♬ Brilliant sunshine which fills the window streams in ♬

200
00:17:14,850 --> 00:17:20,170
♬ Like a dream. Like a Dream ♬

201
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:30,590
Honey. What's wrong with you these days? Are you worried about something?

202
00:17:30,590 --> 00:17:34,610
If you don't have an appetite, tell me what you want to eat. You'll lose weight if you keep going on like this.

203
00:17:34,610 --> 00:17:37,380
- Everything went okay with Louis going to work?
- Yeah.

204
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:40,530
- There was nothing strange about him?
- No. Why?

205
00:17:40,530 --> 00:17:46,280
Nothing. If he's at the company, then he should come see me.

206
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:48,630
Making me worry...

207
00:17:48,630 --> 00:17:52,110
Why are you so worried about Louis?

208
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:54,950
When did I say that I was worried about him?!

209
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:59,210
You just said that you were worried about him.

210
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,490
Honey!

211
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:12,190
Seems like Dad gets mad at you all the time.

212
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:15,420
He followed me around begging to marry him, as if he were going to die if I didn't. So I did.

213
00:18:15,420 --> 00:18:17,780
I feel so wronged.

214
00:18:17,780 --> 00:18:20,770
Mother, did Louis arrive?

215
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:23,050
But, Seon Gu, you went to pick him up.

216
00:18:23,050 --> 00:18:26,500
Louis took the car and left alone.

217
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,820
You can drive, right?

218
00:18:31,650 --> 00:18:35,640
Exactly how much does he remember?

219
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:40,380
No one can find out that I made him drive.

220
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:44,320
Joong Won!

221
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:46,700
Hey! Where are you?! Get out here this instant!

222
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:49,560
What happened for you to be yelling so much?

223
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:52,750
You little rascal! Take this!

224
00:18:53,890 --> 00:18:56,250
Hey, why are you doing this? Dad! Stop Mom!

225
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:59,460
I'm on Mom's side today.

226
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:05,060
You are not an eighth-grader, but you quit a respectable director position and what?!

227
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:07,420
Daddy Long Legs?

228
00:19:15,010 --> 00:19:19,550
I'm giving myself a sabbatical for the next one year.

229
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:24,690
I spent all that time just looking forward and running. I really wanted to rest.

230
00:19:24,690 --> 00:19:28,700
I wanted to put down everything for once and think about

231
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:32,880
whether I've lived well and how I should live my life from now on.

232
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:37,930
That Daddy Long Legs position is my side job that I took on to invest in people, while I'm on my sabbatical.

233
00:19:37,930 --> 00:19:42,260
That girl managed to sell wild ginseng to me at midnight in Seoul Station.

234
00:19:42,260 --> 00:19:43,900
To me of all people.

235
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:47,520
Do I look like someone who would buy something from a sundry peddler?

236
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:54,020
First! Bring that girl here.

237
00:19:54,020 --> 00:19:54,790
Why?

238
00:19:54,790 --> 00:19:57,240
I'm sooo curious!

239
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:15,720
It feels like it keeps getting heavier...

240
00:20:17,830 --> 00:20:19,820
Maybe not?

241
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:23,710
It can't be.

242
00:20:31,290 --> 00:20:33,250
Bok Sil!

243
00:20:34,340 --> 00:20:35,920
Sil Sil Bok Sil!

244
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:38,540
- Just a sec, Oppa!
- Sil Sil Bok Sil!

245
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:40,720
- Just a minute!
- Open the door!

246
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:42,220
Welcome, Oppa.

247
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:45,050
- Welcome, Ahjumma.
- Bok Sil.

248
00:20:45,050 --> 00:20:50,000
I made tons of side dishes so I had leftovers.

249
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,050
You can have these.

250
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:55,550
I just brought the fruits too because they looked like they'd go bad if not eaten soon.

251
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:57,230
In Seong, put these in the fridge.

252
00:20:57,230 --> 00:21:00,030
This is bone soup made with 2-for-1 packages of Korean beef.

253
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:04,120
I don't know what I was thinking! I made so much bone soup, I don't have room for it in my fridge.

254
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:06,720
- Slurp it up with some rice every morning before going to work.
- Okay.

255
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:09,620
I'm only giving you these because I had too much, so don't feel bad about it.

256
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:11,940
Ok. Thank you, Ahjumma.

257
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:13,470
My mom is large-handed.

258
00:21:13,470 --> 00:21:15,520
- I am large-handed.
- She also has a big butt.

259
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:17,220
Big-butt-- you!

260
00:21:18,810 --> 00:21:20,790
We have so many rooms,

261
00:21:20,790 --> 00:21:25,430
yet I have to sleep with Lady Geum Ja with a divider in between. My life is pretty depressing.

262
00:21:25,430 --> 00:21:28,980
Be quiet! You can't live in a different room

263
00:21:28,980 --> 00:21:31,010
when we can't let Bok Sil suspect anything.

264
00:21:31,010 --> 00:21:34,410
We should be grateful he bought this building for us. What more do you want?

265
00:21:34,410 --> 00:21:36,160
I'm just saying.

266
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:39,720
Why does Louis send such a demanding menu?

267
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:41,950
For tomorrow he wants braised short ribs, japchae, salad kimchi...

268
00:21:41,950 --> 00:21:44,390
These are all really complicated to make!

269
00:21:44,390 --> 00:21:48,640
This Annoying Style little rascal. I'm only holding back because Bok Sil's the one eating it.

270
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:51,810
Those are all my favorite dishes.

271
00:21:52,610 --> 00:21:55,670
Did you happen to write this?

272
00:21:55,670 --> 00:21:57,670
I don't think so.

273
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:01,020
This has perfect spelling, it had to be you.

274
00:22:01,020 --> 00:22:04,640
You! Open this. Open!

275
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:16,800
It's already this late?

276
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:29,190
Bok Sil, I'm not sleepy at all. Can't I stay up for a little longer?

277
00:22:31,130 --> 00:22:37,500
♬ Can it end someday? ♬

278
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:44,490
Louis, how are you?
♬ The wound of the long long tears ♬

279
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:53,150
♬ I draw you and erase you again gently ♬

280
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:57,440
Good night, Bok Sil.

281
00:22:57,440 --> 00:23:09,070
♬ It hurts to see you from behind like this ♬

282
00:23:09,860 --> 00:23:16,820
♬ I can't see you ♬

283
00:23:17,710 --> 00:23:22,160
♬ who are going far away ♬

284
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:25,440
Good night again, Bok Sil.

285
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:32,300
♬ I feel empty ♬

286
00:23:56,930 --> 00:23:58,710
Bok Sil!

287
00:24:00,780 --> 00:24:04,790
I brought some more side dishes. Put them in the refrigerator.

288
00:24:16,910 --> 00:24:20,610
♬  Dream lover ♬
(in Cantonese from the Movie Chungking Express)

289
00:24:20,610 --> 00:24:24,310
♬  A one-minute embrace  ♬

290
00:24:24,310 --> 00:24:28,320
♬  A ten-minute kiss  ♬

291
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:35,450
♬  Strange lover  ♬

292
00:24:35,450 --> 00:24:39,180
♬  How could you walk into my heart  ♬

293
00:24:39,180 --> 00:24:43,470
♬  And create such excitement  ♬

294
00:24:45,490 --> 00:24:49,380
♬  I feel like we had a torrid love affair  ♬

295
00:24:49,380 --> 00:24:51,190
♬  I don't feel like we were ever closer than now  ♬

296
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:53,680
Good night, Bok Sil.

297
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:57,810
♬  Thoughts begin to grow bigger  ♬

298
00:25:02,130 --> 00:25:08,210
I thought Young Master was just a kid but he's so romantic.

299
00:25:08,210 --> 00:25:12,150
How can he be so constant?

300
00:25:12,150 --> 00:25:16,300
Don't you think he learned from me? I'm that kind of a man.

301
00:25:17,380 --> 00:25:19,050
You should learn from him.

302
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:22,790
You have a long way to go to get to his level.

303
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:29,420
Aren't you disappointed that Jo In Seong guy took your chauffeur spot?

304
00:25:29,420 --> 00:25:32,380
I'm getting old so I should start yielding a little.

305
00:25:32,380 --> 00:25:36,260
Instead, I got time to spend with you, Jeong Ran.

306
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:47,150
How is President Baek Seon Gu? Does he still call you?

307
00:25:47,150 --> 00:25:52,700
Yes. He asks me if Young Master Louis's memory has come back, every day.

308
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:56,680
Is there any reason that his memory shouldn't fully come back?

309
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:02,360
So, work is doable?

310
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:08,040
Yes, I get along well with the teammates, and it's my expertise, shopping.

311
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:13,910
Yes. I knew you would be good. I shouldn't be worried.

312
00:26:13,910 --> 00:26:17,260
Have you been to Sunnyland?

313
00:26:17,260 --> 00:26:18,610
Not yet.

314
00:26:18,610 --> 00:26:22,640
It got popular by word-of-mouth and gets really crowded these days.

315
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:28,670
Chairwoman said it was your idea. Is that so?

316
00:26:29,410 --> 00:26:34,730
Ohhhh... I don't recall.

317
00:26:35,460 --> 00:26:39,080
I told Grandma about Sunnyland?

318
00:26:40,810 --> 00:26:47,560
Whoa! Whoa! Ahjussi, I must be a genius!

319
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:49,320
Whoa!

320
00:26:49,950 --> 00:26:56,050
His memory wasn't completely back. It was partial.

321
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:59,270
Right, Ahjussi!

322
00:27:00,540 --> 00:27:05,100
If I hadn't come back, Grandma's shares would have been all yours.

323
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:09,810
I hope it didn't upset you to split the shares in half with me.

324
00:27:10,930 --> 00:27:17,160
No way. I'm so glad you came back.

325
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:19,270
I'm really glad you're here, too.

326
00:27:19,270 --> 00:27:21,830
Please take care of me in the future.

327
00:27:27,490 --> 00:27:30,860
When will this No Name get his consciousness back?

328
00:27:30,860 --> 00:27:32,820
I know, right?

329
00:27:32,820 --> 00:27:36,110
Why did he go into someone else's rooftop room and get this rough treatment?

330
00:27:36,110 --> 00:27:38,620
He needs to wake up so we can ask him.

331
00:27:39,450 --> 00:27:43,890
Do we have to say it's a relief since Louis and Bok Sil didn't get hurt thanks to him?

332
00:27:43,890 --> 00:27:48,130
He is a complicated character for me to figure out.

333
00:27:49,630 --> 00:27:51,280
Daddy-Long-Legs Cha Joong Won

334
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:53,830
I still can't figure the director out.

335
00:27:53,830 --> 00:27:57,750
He seems like he's got all the knowledge in the world,

336
00:27:57,750 --> 00:28:02,250
but then he sometimes seems infinitely lacking, like a bottomless pot.

337
00:28:02,900 --> 00:28:05,050
What are you muttering about all by yourself?

338
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:07,010
You're here?

339
00:28:07,010 --> 00:28:10,540
Ta-da! Do you like it?

340
00:28:11,380 --> 00:28:15,430
Well, it'll do. Good job.

341
00:28:15,430 --> 00:28:17,830
How did your investigation of the schizandra berries in Moon-gyeong go yesterday?

342
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:21,600
Yes. We entered into a contract with Mr. Choi Go Bong, who owns the biggest farm there.

343
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:24,320
The quality of the schizandra berries is top-notch.

344
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:26,080
Did you make sure that his products come with the eco-friendly certification?

345
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,080
Of course.

346
00:28:29,810 --> 00:28:31,110
Come here.

347
00:28:31,110 --> 00:28:32,620
What?

348
00:28:32,620 --> 00:28:34,410
Quickly.

349
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:42,440
Give me your hand.

350
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:45,230
- My hand? Why?
- Hurry up.

351
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:03,140
It got stamped on good.

352
00:29:04,070 --> 00:29:07,850
Why? Did you think I was going to give you a ring or something?

353
00:29:08,450 --> 00:29:11,260
I find these kinds of things amusing these days.

354
00:29:11,260 --> 00:29:15,140
I don't know why I didn't play these kinds of pranks when I was younger.

355
00:29:15,140 --> 00:29:18,390
Director. You're really like a bottomless pot.

356
00:29:18,390 --> 00:29:23,980
What? How dare you call the King of Charisma a bottomless pot?

357
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:29,170
Wow, this is nice!

358
00:29:29,170 --> 00:29:31,320
Detective!

359
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:32,820
Hello.

360
00:29:32,820 --> 00:29:35,840
Hello. Detective Nam, why brings you here?

361
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:40,490
I came to see Bok Sil, of course. I'm late in congratulating you. Congrats on becoming a company president, Bok Sil.

362
00:29:40,490 --> 00:29:41,670
Thank you.

363
00:29:41,670 --> 00:29:44,710
- Hey, where should I put this?
- Please give to me. I'll put it somewhere.

364
00:29:44,710 --> 00:29:48,190
No. It's heavy, so let me do it.

365
00:29:48,190 --> 00:29:50,990
- Then, please put it over there.
- Here?

366
00:29:55,570 --> 00:29:59,260
- You're going to throw this away too, right?
- Yes. You can just put it over here.

367
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:05,560
Thank you.

368
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:09,290
Is there anything else you want me to do? If there's something that you need some muscle for, call me. I'll do it anytime.

369
00:30:09,290 --> 00:30:12,920
You just go and catch some criminals! We're busy, so why would you come in and out of here?

370
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:18,310
Either way, I'm the one doing all the muscles work, so buzz off!

371
00:30:19,180 --> 00:30:20,800
He's kind of weird.

372
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:23,730
Now that I look at you, it looks like you've caught servant's disease.

373
00:30:23,730 --> 00:30:27,950
If we need you, then I'll be the one to call you. Satisfied?

374
00:30:27,950 --> 00:30:32,480
- Servant's Disease?
- He's always been a verbal meanie bottomless pot. So don't worry about him.

375
00:30:32,480 --> 00:30:34,820
Ah, it looks like he has a lot of holes.

376
00:30:34,820 --> 00:30:38,810
- Hey, Go Bok Sil!
- Oh yeah! I also have to separate the garbage, so please help me with that.

377
00:30:38,810 --> 00:30:40,620
Shall I?

378
00:30:51,770 --> 00:30:54,330
Aish, really vexing...

379
00:30:54,380 --> 00:30:58,160
Why are there so many men latching on to Go Bok Sil, harumph...

380
00:31:23,850 --> 00:31:26,150
You worked hard.

381
00:31:33,250 --> 00:31:36,870
- Bok Sil!
- Ahjumma.

382
00:31:36,870 --> 00:31:39,870
Why are you hiding here like some wrongdoer?

383
00:31:39,890 --> 00:31:43,700
No, I just felt comfortable being here like this.

384
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:46,990
Ah, share these with other janitor ahjummas.

385
00:31:47,010 --> 00:31:50,690
These are dried persimmons that just arrived from Mt. Jiri and I brought them because I thought of you.

386
00:31:50,710 --> 00:31:55,620
Dried persimmons from Mt. Jiri? Wow, the ahjummas will happily stuff themselves. Thank you.

387
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:58,160
Now, Oppa In Seong works, too, and you should take it easy at home.

388
00:31:58,190 --> 00:32:00,050
Why do you work yourself so hard?

389
00:32:00,050 --> 00:32:02,100
All four limbs of mine are in a perfect condition. I should make use of them.

390
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:05,370
If a person who's used to physical labor stops all of a sudden, she will actually get sick.

391
00:32:05,370 --> 00:32:07,010
Oh, Ahjumma, really...

392
00:32:07,010 --> 00:32:09,480
Should we dine out the first time in a long while?

393
00:32:09,490 --> 00:32:13,820
I'm sorry. I have a prior engagement today.

394
00:32:22,990 --> 00:32:25,250
Who gave me this?

395
00:32:27,090 --> 00:32:29,690
Did Do Jin give me this?

396
00:32:29,690 --> 00:32:34,160
Team Leader, I love you.
Candidate #1 Byeon Do Jin

397
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:37,690
But Do Jin is like a knockoff Cha Joong Won.

398
00:32:39,390 --> 00:32:41,460
Manager Lee married with four children?

399
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:45,820
Team Leader Baek, accept my heart.
Candidate #2 Lee Gyeong Gook

400
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:48,700
What a grubby idea...

401
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:54,250
- What is this?
- Is it, by any chance...

402
00:32:54,900 --> 00:32:56,690
Louis?

403
00:32:56,690 --> 00:32:59,600
Candidate #3 Louis

404
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:02,420
After breaking up with Go Bok Sil,

405
00:33:02,430 --> 00:33:04,510
does he now like me?

406
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:09,120
The reason he's sitting there is also to see me?

407
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:23,080
Awww, it's so nice...

408
00:33:27,070 --> 00:33:29,970
Ji Sung, would you like to have dinner with me?

409
00:33:29,980 --> 00:33:32,410
There is a good steakhouse nearby.

410
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:34,630
I'm sorry, but maybe next time.

411
00:33:34,630 --> 00:33:36,620
Today I have a tutoring session.

412
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:38,950
Tu-tutoring?

413
00:33:40,210 --> 00:33:44,580
Tutoring, don't you know? Don't you know what tutoring is?

414
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:52,900
How old are you to be receiving tutoring? Hey!

415
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,750
What's the subject, huh?

416
00:33:54,750 --> 00:33:56,830
"Out of options."

417
00:33:56,830 --> 00:33:59,790
Out... of...
(Louis's head band says "Study Hard")

418
00:33:59,790 --> 00:34:05,940
options...

419
00:34:05,940 --> 00:34:09,210
"I collided with a chicken."

420
00:34:09,210 --> 00:34:12,580
I...

421
00:34:12,580 --> 00:34:19,330
col... lie... did...

422
00:34:22,730 --> 00:34:26,050
Aish, so hard. I'm so confused.

423
00:34:26,060 --> 00:34:29,060
If you keep at it a bit longer, your spelling will become perfect, too.

424
00:34:29,060 --> 00:34:31,440
A man who can speak ten languages while spelling beautifully, too...

425
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:34,460
isn't he dashing?

426
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:39,710
I should write Bok Sil a letter when I master spelling.

427
00:34:41,700 --> 00:34:44,850
Of course, I won't actually give it to you, Bok Sil.

428
00:34:54,530 --> 00:34:57,810
Miss Bok Sil, eat a lot.

429
00:34:57,840 --> 00:35:01,410
I did my utmost to prepare these.

430
00:35:01,420 --> 00:35:03,890
Thank you, I will enjoy it.

431
00:35:18,970 --> 00:35:21,900
It's water from brewing Korean hedge nettle.

432
00:35:22,470 --> 00:35:24,110
Do you know Korean hedge nettle?

433
00:35:24,110 --> 00:35:27,530
Of course, it's a good herb for preventing dementia.

434
00:35:27,530 --> 00:35:30,640
You have to cure it well to minimize nutrient loss.

435
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:33,820
Next time, let me dry it for you.

436
00:35:41,980 --> 00:35:45,010
You put in plum syrup instead of sugar.

437
00:35:45,010 --> 00:35:47,070
Plum syrup?!

438
00:35:48,390 --> 00:35:53,220
How did you know I put in plum syrup here?

439
00:35:55,740 --> 00:35:57,890
I just...

440
00:35:57,930 --> 00:36:03,700
thought you added plum syrup, because I tasted plum syrup in the spicy bellflower root side dish.

441
00:36:03,710 --> 00:36:07,680
But if you question me why I said you used plum syrup...

442
00:36:09,150 --> 00:36:13,550
Go Jang Geum
Ten Red Hearts

443
00:36:15,780 --> 00:36:18,640
I said I'd take you home, but you won't have it.

444
00:36:18,670 --> 00:36:23,800
I am more comfortable riding buses. Thank you so much for the dinner invitation.

445
00:36:23,810 --> 00:36:26,760
I will take my leave. Good night.

446
00:36:29,140 --> 00:36:33,930
Okay, when you get home, you must call me and let me know that you've arrived safely.

447
00:36:33,950 --> 00:36:36,950
- Yes, I understand.
- Go Bok Sil,

448
00:36:36,980 --> 00:36:40,990
you are too stubborn.

449
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:43,160
I will get going.

450
00:36:51,940 --> 00:36:55,590
Honey, I will make

451
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:59,300
- that girl into a Jang Geum.
- What?

452
00:36:59,310 --> 00:37:01,490
I can make her my daughter-in-law after making her an oriental medicine doctor.

453
00:37:01,530 --> 00:37:04,560
A daughter-in-law who is a traditional M.D., there is not much to it, after all.

454
00:37:13,340 --> 00:37:17,070
♬ Onara onara aju ona ♬
(Means "Come, come, are you coming for good?" From Jewel in the Palace OST)

455
00:37:17,110 --> 00:37:21,720
My daughter-in-law is Jang Geum!

456
00:37:26,990 --> 00:37:29,090
Yes, this is Nam Joon Hyeok.

457
00:37:30,260 --> 00:37:33,460
Ah, yes, I will come right now.

458
00:37:45,220 --> 00:37:48,760
- It's all finished.
- Thank you every time.

459
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:52,190
Don't mention it. My pleasure.

460
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:55,220
If there is nothing more, I will be on my way.

461
00:37:55,250 --> 00:37:59,720
Ah! Umm, this chair! Would you move it here?

462
00:37:59,720 --> 00:38:01,590
Oh, the chair...

463
00:38:05,330 --> 00:38:08,820
And this table, please turn it this way over here.

464
00:38:08,820 --> 00:38:12,730
And, umm, would you put this chair at the end?

465
00:38:14,620 --> 00:38:19,200
Ahh! Would you move this ladder toward the center?

466
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:21,700
Oh... the ladder...

467
00:38:22,810 --> 00:38:25,770
- Omo, omo, are you okay?
- I'm okay.

468
00:38:28,390 --> 00:38:33,970
But, isn't this a bit odd?

469
00:38:37,620 --> 00:38:42,880
Oh, yes... it's very odd.

470
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:48,830
My heart...

471
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:52,370
is very odd, Mr. Joon Hyeok.

472
00:38:52,380 --> 00:38:57,580
- Then, should I put them back to the original places?
- No.

473
00:38:57,590 --> 00:39:01,620
I should... just let them be as they are.

474
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:12,370
There was no news of rain.

475
00:39:13,820 --> 00:39:17,690
- You don't have an umbrella, right?
- No.

476
00:39:17,690 --> 00:39:20,170
Then, I will take you home.

477
00:39:20,190 --> 00:39:23,690
Since the weather turned cold, you will catch a cold if you get rained on.

478
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:37,400
Wh-Wh-Why are you crying?

479
00:39:37,420 --> 00:39:40,670
Did I perhaps do something wrong?

480
00:39:43,410 --> 00:39:46,820
How long has it been...

481
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:49,660
since I heard such warm words?

482
00:39:52,460 --> 00:39:54,480
Thank you so much

483
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:58,320
for being so kind to me.

484
00:40:19,020 --> 00:40:20,680
Bok Sil!

485
00:40:34,300 --> 00:40:40,790
♬ In a few seconds I am exploding. You can't stop me ♬
♬ Broken Timer Switch ♬

486
00:40:40,790 --> 00:40:44,690
Why isn't Go Bok Sil calling me to tell me that she arrived home safely?

487
00:40:44,690 --> 00:40:48,050
